Title: Official 'Putting the Teens in TMNT' Featurette
Description:
Join producer/writer/"Bebop" star Seth Rogen and director/co-writer Jeff Rowe, along with stars Nicolas Cantu (Leonardo), Shamon Brown Jr. (Mikey), Micah Abbey (Donnie), Brady Noon (Raph), for a behind-the-scenes look at Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Mutant Mayhem, including a discussion about the Ninja Turtles, the personalities of the characters, and the teens bringing their energy to their roles. The film also stars Hannibal Buress, Rose Byrne, Nicolas Cantu, John Cena, Jackie Chan, Ice Cube, Natasia Demetriou, Ayo Edebiri, Giancarlo Esposito, Post Malone, Paul Rudd, and Maya Rudolph.After years of being sheltered from the human world, the Turtle brothers set out to win the hearts of New Yorkers and be accepted as normal teenagers through heroic acts. Their new friend April O’Neil helps them take on a mysterious crime syndicate, but they soon get in over their heads when an army of mutants is unleashed upon them. 
The film's screenplay is by Seth Rogen & Evan Goldberg & Jeff Rowe and Dan Hernandez & Benji Samit. The story is by Brendan O'Brien and Seth Rogen & Evan Goldberg & Jeff Rowe. It is produced by Seth Rogen, p.g.a., Evan Goldberg, p.g.a., and James Weaver, p.g.a., and executive producers are Ramsay McBean and Josh Fagen.
Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Mutant Mayhem, directed by Jeff Rowe and co-directed by Kyler Spears, opens in UK cinemas on July 31, and in US theaters on August 2, 2023.
